chnology located in atlanta georgia ncr was founded in  and acquired by att in  a restructuring of att in  led to ncrs reestablishment january  as a separate company and involved the spinoff of lucent technologies from attcitation needed ncr is the only att spinoff company that has retained its original name—all the others have either been purchased or renamed following subsequent mergerscitation needed contents  history  early years  american selling force  expansion  postwar  small computers  ncr xxx series  ncr xx series  ncr selfserv    series  att  independence  under bill nutis management  products and services  hardware  services  obsolete  senior management  see also  references  external links historyedit early yearsedit antique threecolumn fullkeyboard cash register old national cash register on display at the museo de la secretaría de hacienda y crédito público in mexico city the company began as the national manufacturing company of dayton ohio was established to manufacture and sell the first mechanical cash register invented in  by james ritty in  the company and patents were bought by john henry patterson and his brother frank jefferson patterson and the firm was renamed the national cash register company patterson formed ncr into one of the first modern american companies by introducing new aggressive sales methods and business techniques he established the first sales training school in  and introduced a comprehensive social welfare program for his factory workers other significant figures in the early history of the company were charles f kettering thomas j watson sr and edward a deeds deeds and kettering went on to found dayton engineering laboratories company which later became delco products division of general motors watson eventually worked his way up to general sales manager at an uninspiring sales meeting watson interrupted saying the trouble with every one of us is that we dont think enough we dont get paid for working with our feet — we get paid for working with our heads watson then wrote think on the easel signs with this motto were erected in factory buildings sales offices and club rooms during the mids think later became a widely known symbol of ibm patterson fired watson in  kettering designed the first cash register powered by an electric motor in  within a few years he developed the class  register which was in production for  years and the ok telephone credit authorization system for verifying credit in department storescitation needed american selling forceedit when john h patterson and his brother took over the company cash registers were expensive  usd and only about a dozen of rittys incorruptible cashier machines were in use there was little demand for the expensive device but patterson believed the product would sell once shopkeepers understood it would drastically decrease theft by salesclerks he created a sales team known as the american selling force which worked on commissions and followed a standard sales script the ncr primer the philosophy was to sell a business function rather than just a piece of machinery sales demonstrations were set up in hotels away from the distractions of the buyers business depicting a store interior complete with real merchandise and real cash the sale prospect was described as the pp or probable purchaser once initial objections were swept aside and the pp admitted to internal theft losses the product was demonstrated along with large business charts and diagrams the deal was sealed with a  cent cigar expansionedit ncr expanded quickly and became multinational in  between  and  it acquired a number of smaller cash register companies by  it had sold one million machines and grown to almost  employees combined with rigorous legal attacks pattersons methods enabled the company to fight off bankruptcy buyout over  of its early competitors and achieve control of  of the us market in  the company was found guilty of violating the sherman antitrust act patterson deeds watson and  other ncr executives and managers were convicted of illegal anticompetitive sales practices and were sentenced to one year of imprisonment their convictions were unpopular with the public due to the efforts of patterson and watson to help those affected by the dayton ohio floods of  but efforts to have them pardoned by president woodrow wilson were unsuccessful however their convictions were overturned on appeal in  on the grounds that important defense evidence should have been admitted wwii ncr poster two million units were sold by  the year john patterson died in  ncr went public with an issue of  million in stock at that time the largest public offering in united states history during the first world war ncr manufactured fuses and aircraft instrumentation and during world war ii built aeroengines bomb sights and codebreaking machines including the american bombe designed by joseph desch postwaredit ncr  computer building on its wartime experience with secret communication systems high speed counters and cryptanalytic equipment ncr became a major postwar force in developing new computing and communications technology in  chemists barrett k green and lowell schleicher of ncr in dayton submitted a patent pressure responsive record materials for a carbonless copy paper this became us patent  and was commercialized as ncr paper in february  the company acquired the computer research corporation crc after which it created a specialized electronics division in  ncr introduced its first electronic device the class  posttronic a bank machine using magnetic stripe technology with the general electric company known now just as ge  the company manufactured its first transistorbased computer in  the ncr  also in the s ncr introduced micr magnetic ink character recognition and the ncr  accounting machines in  ncr introduced the ncr electronic data processing system which included the cram storage device the first automated mass storage alternative to magnetic tape libraries accessed manually by computer operators the ncr  and  computers were also offered to customers who did not need the full power of the  the ncr  accepted four types of input magnetic ledger cards punched cards punched tape and keyboard entry with a tape read speed of  characters a second the companys first allintegrated circuit computer was the century  of  the century  was added in  the line was extended through the century  the century series was followed by the criterion series in  ncrs first virtual machine system during this period ncr also produced the  minicomputer for inhouse use it was the compute engine for the  and  accounting machines several generations of instore and inbank controllers and the xxxx imos cobol systems the  also powered peripheral controllers including the  disk subsystem and the  communications processor by  the number of mainframe makers had dropped from  ibm and the seven dwarfs to  ibm and the bunch to  ibm unisys ncr and control data corporation the company adopted the name ncr corporation in  small computersedit in  ncr became involved in open systems architecture its first such system was the unixpowered tower  the success of which approximately  were sold established ncr as a pioneer in bringing industry standards and open systems architecture to the computer market these series systems were based on motorola k cpus and supported ncrs proprietary transaction processing system tmx which was mainly used by financial institutions this product line also saw the first time ncr had offered its products through other than its own direct sales channels since the early s formally added to its company structure in march  ncrs oem systems division spearheaded the design sales revenue and market awareness and acceptance of ncrs tower family part of the cause of this success was the decision by ncr senior management to hire reseller industry veterans for key positions within the fledgling operation and have that unit work with but not answerable to ncrs traditional management structure the industry shift from minicomputers brought personnel with minicomputer and reseller backgrounds such as the division head dan kiegler exdatapoint marketing marketing manager and later director of field sales dave lang exdec reseller marketing director and salesperson and other critical contributors at corporate levels who then hired a complementary field sales organization primarily made up of proven people from dec wang and other faltering minicomputer firms ncr office buildings in augsburg germany in the s ncr sold various pc compatible atclass computers like the small ncr called an intelligent terminal they proposed a customized version of msdos named ncrdos which for example offered support for switching the cpu between   or  mhz speeds the computers featured an improved cga adapter the nga which had a × text mode more suitable for business uses than the original × mode with characters drawn using singlepixelwide lines giving an appearance similar to that of classic ibm  terminals the additional fourcolor × graphical mode was identical to cgas × mode from a programming point of view ncr also manufactured two proprietary series of minitomidrange computers iseries  idps operating system  and  imos operating system  and  irx operating system     ip    ip    system  models        itx operating system these were i interactive computers allowing tty terminals to be connected later models supported all industrystandard communication protocols vseries  vrx operating system and  vrxe operating system these were v series comparable to mainframes supporting page mode terminals the hardware did have similarities with the iseries while the operating system and user interface was totally different in  ncr introduced the system  a sevenlevel family of computers based on intels  and  cpus the majority of the system  range utilised ibms micro channel architecture rather than the more prevalent isa architecture and utilised scsi peripherals as well as the more popular parallel and serial port interfaces resulting in a premium product with premium pricing the  through ncr subsidiary applied digital data systems supported both the pick operating system and prime information the s saw the widespread installations of the model  in national westminster and barclays banks throughout the uk but it was not until the model  developed at its dundee plant in scotland and introduced in  that the company began to make more serious inroads into the atm market subsequent models included the  and xx personas series in early  the company launched its new generation of atms—the xx selfserv series ncr currently commands over a third of the entire atm market with an estimated  trillion being withdrawn from ncr atms every year in addition ncrs expertise in this field led the company to contract with the us military to support the eagle cash program with customized atms ncr xxx seriesedit the ncr xxxseries is the range of atms produced by ncr from the early s most models were designed and initially manufactured at its dundee factory in scotland but later produced at several other locations around the world there have been several distinct generations xxseries the initial models introduced in  were the  interior vestibule and  through the wall or ttw introduced a number of features which have become standard among atms—chiefly the individual functions of the atm are divided among discrete modules which can be easily removed and replaced for repair or replenishment the  featured the standard antivandal smoked perspex screen which covered the keypad and screen until the cardholder inserted their card the enhanced  ttw model appeared in  and had an improved antivandal fascia and was the first atm to dispense with the need for the retracting perspex screen the  offered the first crude deposit function with the machine supplying the deposit envelopes which were subsequently stored in the machines safe for subsequent back office processing xxseries produced from  to  enhanced functions such as colour displays and improved security and usability functions became available the introduction of media entry indicators mei which highlight the card entry slot to the customer was also a part of this series some xx machines produced between – were badged as att rather than ncr mirroring the companys brief ownership under the telecoms giant in the mids xx models have included the  interior lobby cash dispense only  interior lobby multifunction—dispense  deposit  exterior ttw dispense only  exterior ttw driveup multifunction and  exterior ttw multifunction xxseries marketed as personas from  to the present these models were characterised by the gradual move towards greater atm functionality including intelligent envelopeless deposit by means of automated cheque recognition modules coin dispense and electronic cash recognition functions which allows bank customers to deposit cash and cheques with instant processing of the transaction the xx series has also been characterised by the gradual introduction of lcd displays instead of the traditional crt monitor models have included the  compact interior lobby dispense only  interior lobby with cash accept  deposit only  exterior ttw cash dispense  multifunction ttw the latest ttw versions of the personas line introduced in  and marketed as mseries added functions such as cash recycling coin dispense barcode reading a larger  lcd display with touchscreen option and for the first time a common wall footprint for both the multifunction  or single function  ncr xx seriesedit ncrs th generation of atms have been noted for the further move towards intelligent deposit and the expansion of secondary functions such as barcode reading xseries marketed under the personas mseries brand were introduced in  to the present these models consist of the  interior lobby multifunction and  throughthewall multifunction the outlook design is very different from the personas model on the frontaccess s the front cover is opened upwards which claim to be saving the services area ncr selfserv    seriesedit ncrs latest atm services introduced in  this series is a complete redesign of both outlook and technological contents it is also a cost down product selfserv  series are singlefunction eg cashout atms while selfserv  series are fullfunction cashout and intelligent deposit machines attedit ncr was acquired september   by att corporation for  billion and was joined with teradata corporation on february   as an att subsidiary its  yearend headcount was  employees and contractors by  the subsidiary produced a yearend  billion net loss on  billion in revenue the net losses continued in  and  losses that required repeated subsidies from the parent company and resulted in a  yearend headcount of  during these three years att was the former ncrs largest customer accounting for over  billion in revenue on february   the company sold its microelectronics division and storage systems division to hyundai which named it symbios logic at the time it was the largest purchase of an american company by a korean company for a while starting in  the subsidiary was renamed att global information solutions but in  att decided to spin off the company and in  changed its name back to ncr in preparation for the spinoff the company outlined its reasons for the spinoff in an information statement sent to its stockholders which cited in addition to changes in customer needs and need for focused management time and attention the following advantages of vertical integration which had motivated atts earlier acquisition of ncr are outweighed by its costs and disadvantagesto varying degrees many of the actual and potential customers of lucent and ncr are or will be competitors of atts communications services businesses ncr believes that its efforts to target the communications industry have been hindered by the reluctance of atts communications services competitors to make purchases from an att subsidiary ncr reemerged as a standalone company on january   independenceedit one of ncrs first significant acquisitions after becoming independent from att came in july  when it purchased compris technologies a privately held company in kennesaw georgia that produced software for restaurant chains in november  ncr purchased dataworks inc a person privately held company in san antonio texas the montgomery county historical society and ncr corporation joined in  into an innovative partnership committed to preserving the voluminous ncr archive for more than three months in late  trucks traveled between ncrs building  and the historical societys research center taking three million pieces of an extraordinary collection to their new home in  ncr sold its computer hardware manufacturing assets to solectron and ceased to produce generalpurpose computer systems focusing instead on the retail and financial industries in  ncr acquired customer relationship management provider ceres integrated solutions and services company front technologies recent acquisitions include selfservice companies kinetics infoamerica and galvanon and software company decisionpoint in april  ncr purchased copient technologies an indianabased retail marketing software company under bill nutis managementedit ncr world headquarters in duluth ga ncr office building in duluth georgia in  ncr acquired software company idvelocity and the atm manufacturing division of tidel a cash security equipment manufacturer specializing in retail markets on january   ncr announced its intention to separate into two independent companies by spinning off teradata to shareholders bill nuti would continue his role as president and ceo of ncr while teradata senior vp mike koehler would assume leadership of teradata on october   ncr corporation and teradata jointly announced the teradata business unit spinoff was complete with michael koehler as the first ceo of teradata on january   ncr announced plans to restructure its entire atm manufacturing operations with  jobs at its dundee plant being cut a further  jobs were cut in waterloo ontario canada in  the dundee manufacturing facility was closed along with plants in são paulo and bucharest citing global economic conditions as the reason ncr extended its selfservice portfolio into the digital media market with the january  announcement of ncr xpress entertainment a multichannel entertainment kiosk ncr’s acquisition of touch automation llc was announced on december   on october   ncr announced a global reseller partnership with experticity a seattlebased software company in  ncr relocated its corporate headquarters from dayton ohio to duluth georgia this news was shocking as dayton served as ncrs home for  years in  ncr became the second largest dvd kiosk operator in north america with the acquisitions of the new release and dvd play in  ncr completed the acquisition of digital signage company netkey in august  ncr purchased radiant systems a hospitality and retail systems company for us billion radiants hospitality division turned into a new hospitality line of business within ncr radiants petroleum and convenience retail business became part of its retail line of business several radiant executives remained on board including scott kingsfield who was a general manager of ncrs retail line of business and left ncr in  and andy heyman who became general manager of ncrs financial services line of business in august  the company was hit with charges of avoiding us economic sanctions against syria greatly affecting its stock price in february  ncr completed its acquisition of retalix nasdaq rtlx a provider of retail software and services for approximately  million in cash in january  ncr completed its acquisition of digital insight corporation a provider of online and mobile banking to midmarket financial institutions from equity firm thoma bravo llc for  billion in cash in september  mark benjamin was named president and chief operating officer of ncr benjamin is a year veteran of human resources management and will report directly to bill nuti products and servicesedit ncrs rd activity is split between its three major centres in atlanta usa retail dundee scotland financial industry and waterloo ontario it also has rd centres in beijing cebu philippines belgrade  serbia puducherry and hyderabad in india ncr also has manufacturing facility in beijing budapest and also the indian territory of puducherry which is a regional manufacturing and export hub hardwareedit ncr fastlane in use at a virginia walmart store item processing platforms mainly checks  itran  ts pcs system  point of sale pos for retail and food service pos displays pos printers pos touch screens pos terminals ncr silver complete pointofsale that runs on ipad iphone or ipod touch device pos self checkout ncr selfserv checkout formerly ncr fastlane pos scanners selfservice hardware atms and kiosks easypoint personas selfserv servers s s system  tower servicesedit ebusiness education it infrastructure services managed services payment retail selfservice obsoleteedit class  register class  bank posting machine c  ncr voyager an i smp computer platform that preceded intels smp specification electronic shelf labels realprice  discontinued  senior managementedit ceo bill nuti august  – present ceo mark hurd – ceo lars nyberg – ceo jerre stead – company renamed att gis ceo charles e exley jr – ceo william s anderson – ceo robert s oelman – ceo stanley c allyn – ceo edward a deeds – ceo frederick beck patterson – ceo john h patterson – interim ceo jim ringler  interim ceo bill oshea  interim ceo gil williamson  see alsoedit atlanta portal companies portal ncr book award referencesedit  company histories ncr corporation funding universe retrieved february     boone christian  chapman dan june   ncr move a burst of good news amid recession georgia spending  million in tax breaks incentives to a